x4freetext: Experiment perfomed at the TUNL tandem
Natural copper targets with diameter of 18.9-mm and
thickness between 1.0 and 2.5 mm. Disks were
supported by a thin plastic foil and mounted at 0deg
relative to the incident charged-particle beam at a
distance of 2.5 cm from the end of the deuterium gas
cell. To measure the neutron fluence, indium monitor
foils of the same cross-sectional area and 0.125-mm
thickness were attached to the front and back faces of
the copper disk. The copper target and associated
monitor foils were surrounded by a thin-walled cage
made of cadmium (0.25-mm wall thickness) to eliminate
the effect of thermal neutrons on the cross-section
purity germanium (HPGe) detectors was used to
